results.name: a(n) = smallest positive m such that 2n-1 | 10^m-1, or 0 if no such m exists.
comment: This is yet another version of the sequences defined in A002329, A007732, A070682, A084680. - _N. J. A. Sloane_, Sep 08 2012
a(n) gives the multiplicative order of 10 mod (2n-1), if it is finite, or 0 if not defined.
link: V. Raman, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..100.
